						<summary>

						<p>This record in archaic characters is not dated and belongs to the reign of the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">[Kī]rttivarma-Satyāśraya,</hi> probably the second king of that name. He is stated to have remitted certain taxes due from some <hi rend="italic">Gāmuṇḍas</hi> (who are named). He also gave them the umbrella and other honours.</p>						

						</summary>
